Ac'r III. SCENE 3.

Chremes enters on his way to Simo's house, in consequence of a report which has reached his ears that his daughter is to be married to Pamphilus on that very day. He is in no good humour, but Simo manages to talk him over, and Chremes agrees to the match on the assurance that Pamphilus has really broken off all connexion with Glycerium, a statement which Davos is summoned to corroborate.
